1.4. User also acknowledges and agrees that with respect to certain activities, the collection, transfer, storage, and processing of User information may be undertaken by trusted third party partners or affiliates or agents of Borzo India such as credit card processors, insurance companies, web hosting providers, communication services, and web analytic providers, to help facilitate Borzo India in providing certain functions.
1.5. Unless stated otherwise, this Privacy Policy applies to all information that is disclosed by the User on the Site/App/Сourier App (hereinafter
“Platform"
).
2.1. Borzo India may collect and use, information that can be used to identify or contact a Person (“
Personal Information
"), including but not limited to Personal Information as enumerated below:
2.1.1. When the User browses or accesses the Platform directly, Borzo India collects information from the User, including but not limited to Personal Information. For instance, when User requests for information on the Platform, submits or uploads information or Content on the Platform, seeks to register on the Platform, Borzo India collects information which may include where permitted by Applicable Law, the following Personal Information:
(i) name;
(ii) email;
(iii) telephone number;
(iv) postal address;
(v) profile picture;
(vi) payment method;
(vii) items requested for Borzo Services; and
(viii) other information chosen to be provided by the User.
2.1.2. Information automatically collected
In compliance with Applicable Law in order for the User to access and use the Borzo Services, information which may be collected by Borzo India (or third parties acting on its behalf) by automated means includes:
(i)
Location Information:
When User uses the Borzo Services, Borzo India collects precise location data about the delivery of goods from the Platform entered into by the User. If the User permits Borzo India to access location services through the permission system used by the User's mobile operating system, Borzo India may also collect the precise location of the Device when the Platform is running in the foreground or background. Borzo India may also derive the approximate location of the Device's IP address.
(ii)
Contacts Information:
If the User permits the Platform to access the address book on the Device through the permission system on the User's mobile operating system, Borzo India may access and store names and contact information from the User's address book to facilitate social interactions through the Borzo Services and for other purposes described in this Privacy Policy or at the time of consent or collection.
(iii)
Transaction Information:
Borzo India collects transaction details related to the use of Borzo Services, including the type of service requested, date and time the Borzo Services were provided, amounts charged, distance of delivery and other related transaction details.
(iv)
Usage and Preference Information:
Borzo India collects information about how the User and Platform visitors interact with the Borzo Services, preferences expressed, and settings chosen. In some cases, Borzo India does this through the use of cookies, pixel tags and similar technologies that create and maintain unique identifiers.
(v)
Device Information:
Borzo India may collect information about the User's Device, including for example, the hardware model, operating system and version, software and file names and various, preferred language, unique device identifier, advertising identifiers, serial number, device motion information and mobile network information.
(vi)
Call and SMS Data:
Borzo Services facilitate communications between Users. In connection with facilitating the Borzo Services, Borzo India receives call data, including the date and time of the call or SMS message, the Users' phone numbers, and the content of the SMS message.
(vii)
Log Information:
When the User interacts with Borzo India to avail Borzo Services, Borzo India collects server logs, which may include information like Device IP address, access dates and times, App features or pages viewed, App crashes and other system activity, type of browser and third party site or service the User was using before interacting with Borzo Services.
2.1.3. Information collected from other sources
Borzo India may also receive information from other sources and combine that with the information collected through the Borzo Services. For example:
(i) If User chooses to link, create, or log in to User's account on the Platform with a payment provider (for example, Google Wallet) or social media service (for example, Facebook) or if you engage with a separate app or website that uses Borzo India's API (or whose API Borzo India uses), Borzo India may receive information about the User or User's connections from that website or app.
(ii) When User requests on demand services, Borzo India's Couriers may provide Borzo India with a User rating after providing Borzo Services to the Client.
(iii) If User also interacts with Borzo Services in another capacity, for instance as user of other apps Borzo India provides, Borzo India may combine or associate that information with information Borzo India has collected from the User in their capacity as User.
3.1. “
Sensitive Personal Information
" refers to Personal Information revealing racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religious or philosophical beliefs, or trade union membership, and the processing of genetic data, biometric data for the purpose of uniquely identifying a natural person, data concerning health or data concerning a natural person's sex life or sexual orientation.
3.2. Borzo India does not require / collect / process Sensitive Personal Information of the User.
4.1. Personal Information submitted to the Platform will be used for the purposes specified in this Privacy Policy or on the Platform.
4.2. Borzo India may use the Personal Information collected from the User to:
(i) provide, maintain, and improve Borzo Services, including, for example, to facilitate payments, facilitate insurance provision to the Courier by TSP, send receipts, provide products and services requested by the User (and send related information), develop new features, provide customer support to Users, develop safety features, authenticate Users, and send product updates and administrative messages;
(ii) perform internal operations, including, for example, to prevent fraud and abuse of Borzo Services; to troubleshoot software bugs and operational problems; to conduct data analysis, testing, and research; and to monitor and analyse usage and activity trends;
(iii) send or facilitate communications (i) between Client and the Courier; (ii) between the Courier and a contact of Client to whom the Client wishes to deliver the goods; and (iii) between Client and contact of the Client whom the Client wishes to deliver the goods at Client's direction in connection with the use of certain features, such as expected date and time of delivery of goods, name and details of the Courier who will be providing Borzo Services;
(iv) send the User communications which Borzo India thinks will be of interest to the User, including information about products, services, promotions, news, and events of Borzo India and other companies, where permissible and according to local applicable laws, and to process contest, sweepstake, or other promotion entries and fulfil any related awards; and
(v) personalise and improve Borzo Services, including to provide or recommend features, content, social connections, referrals, and advertisements.
4.3. Borzo India uses the User's usage data (“
Usage Data
") to help diagnose problems with and maintain computer servers, to manage the Platform, and to enhance the Platform and Borzo Services based on the usage pattern data received.
4.4. Borzo India may generate reports and analysis based on the Usage Data for internal analysis, monitored and marketing solutions.
4.5. Borzo India may provide Usage Data to third parties, but when it does so, it does not provide personally – identifying information without User's permission.
5.1. Borzo India uses data collection services such as “cookies" on the Platform to help analyse the Borzo India Platform flow, measure promotional effectiveness, and promote trust and safety. Borzo India offers certain features that are only available through the use of a “cookie". Borzo India also offers cookies to allow the User to enter its password less frequently during a session. Cookies can also help Borzo India to provide information that is targeted to the User's interests. Most cookies are “session cookies", meaning that they are automatically deleted from the User's hard drive at the end of a session. Users are always free to decline Borzo India cookies if the User's browser permits, although in that case the User may not be able to use certain features on the Platform and the User may be required to re-enter its password more frequently during a session. A “cookie" is a small piece of information stored by a web server on a web browser, so it can be later read back from that browser. Cookies are useful for enabling the browser to remember information specific to a given User. Borzo India places both permanent and temporary cookies in User's computer hard drive. The cookies do not contain any of User's personally identifiable information.
5.2. When Users register themselves on the Platform, Borzo India creates User's account, assigning a personal identification number, this personal identification number is then sent back to User's hard drive in the form of a “cookie", which is a small bit of code. This code is unique to each User. It enables seamless travel across the Platform, allowing User to use the Platform without having to enter its password frequently or fill out registration forms with information User has already provided.
6.1. Sharing of Personal Information
6.1.1. Borzo India may share User's Personal Information with:
(i) The Couriers to enable them to provide the Courier Services. For example, Borzo India may share the Client's name, average Client rating given by other Couriers, and pick up and delivery locations of goods / parcels with the Couriers;
(ii) general public if the User submits content on a public forum, such as blog comments, social media posts, or other features of Borzo Services that are viewable by the general public; and
(iii) third parties with whom the User chooses to let Borzo India share information, for example, other apps or websites that integrate with Borzo India's API or Borzo Services or those with API or Service which are integrated by Borzo India;
(iv) third parties with whom the Courier chooses to let Borzo India share information, including Clients, insurance agents and insurers.
6.2. Other Important Sharing
6.2.1. Borzo India may share User's Information with:
(i) Borzo India's subsidiaries and affiliated entities that provide services or conduct data processing on behalf of Borzo India or for data centralisation and / or logistics purposes;
(ii) vendors, consultants, marketing partners, insurance service providers, communication service providers, and other service providers who need access to such information to carry out work on behalf of Borzo India or to enter further to the agreement with the Couriers individually;
(iii) in response to a request for information, by a competent authority, summons, court orders or other legal or quasi – judicial processes if Borzo India believes that disclosure is in accordance with or is otherwise required by, any applicable law, regulation, or legal process;
(iv) law enforcement officials, government authorities, or other third parties if Borzo India believes the User's actions are inconsistent with the Terms, Privacy Policy or any other policies of Borzo India to protect the rights, property or safety of Borzo India or others;
(v) respond to claims that an advertisement, posting or other content violates the rights of a third party; or protect the rights, property or personal safety of the User or the general public;
(vi) in connection with, or during negotiations of any merger, sale of company assets, consolidation or restructuring, financing or acquisition of all or a portion of Borzo India's business by or into another company;
(vii) if Borzo India otherwise notifies the User and User consents to the sharing; and
(viii) in an aggregated and / or anonymised form which cannot reasonably be used to identify the User.
6.3. Borzo India may share Personal Information with its affiliates and authorised agents, representatives, auditors, and advisors to help detect and prevent identity theft, fraud, and other potentially illegal acts; correlate related or multiple accounts to prevent abuse of Borzo Services; and to facilitate joint or co-branded services that the User requests where such services are provided by more than one corporate entity. Those entities and affiliates may not market to the User as a result of such sharing unless the User explicitly opts-in.
